tldr: The user requested a review of their sleep questionnaire application
  against acceptance criteria and a detailed plan for missing features. The plan
  was successfully implemented, adding critical functionalities like a tiredness
  severity scale, COMISA detection, insufficient sleep syndrome detection,
  weighted EDS scoring, expanded CSV export, and pain/chronic fatigue screening.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application to ensure it met all specified acceptance criteria. Following an
  initial assessment that identified several gaps, a detailed plan was created.
  The implementation phase focused on addressing these identified missing
  features. Key additions included a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness, complete
  with safety warnings for high scores, and the integration of detection logic
  for specific sleep disorders like COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. The
  reporting capabilities were enhanced with weighted EDS scoring and the
  inclusion of placeholder outbound links to external resources. Furthermore,
  the data export functionality was significantly improved by expanding the CSV
  export to encompass all questionnaire responses. New questions were also added
  to screen for pain severity and chronic fatigue symptoms, providing a more
  holistic assessment. The project successfully brought the application closer
  to the full requirements outlined in the SOW and questionnaire specification.
